In the Pre Series of 1911's there is less than 2% of these pistols that were Nickel finished.That makes the factory finished pistols very difficult to find. This Colt also has a factory letter that states the nickelfinish and that it was shipped to the Johnson Plantation Gun Shop in Ashburn Georgia February 9 1970. This Colt isfitted with stunning original pearl grips. The pistol itself shows very little handling or being fired. The high polish sideshave a mirror finish that would rate a 99% overall condition. The top of the slide and frame sides would rate a 98+%overall condition. The magazine is the correct original magazine for this pistol. The barrel shows no plating loss orwear. The high quality reproduction box has the correct end label with the correct nickel finish tag. This is one of the nicest condition 1911's that any collector would be proud to have in their collection!FEEL FREE TO MAKE AN OFFER!!

title: For Sale:  Norinco 213 9mm Tokarev clone
postcontent: This is a Norinco 213, This is a 9mm copy of the TT33, a rugged battle proven Soviet classic that was originally chambered in 7.62x25mm. This piece is in very good condition with some 400 rounds fired through it. Includes 3x 8 round magazines. A rubber combat grip is installed which greatly enhances pointability and control. Being a single stack design it is thin and easy for smaller hands to grip onto. The low recoil of the 9mm combined with the all steel construction and ergonomic grip make this gun a soft shooter. A locked breech single action design similar to the Browning 1911 makes it strong enough to run NATO spec +P+ 9mm. With the proper barrel and magazine it can be easily converted to the original 7.62 chambering, and conversion barrels in .38 super can be found as well.The feed ramp and rails have been polished to smooth operation and aid feed reliabilty. This version is one of the later imports and uses the dedicated "skinny" type 9mm magazines. Standard 7.62x25 Tokarev magazines can be used by removing the spacer within the magazine well.
